Dear Martin,

Thanks a lot for your feedback to my request. We will try your improved
version of the USE tool indeed. Regarding the ocl_uml2.use file, it has a
minor bug:

use> open ocl_uml2.use
ocl_uml2.use:4871:2: expecting EOF, found 'context'

Although the failure message is not very instructive, I found this bug is
due to an empty context clause. By just commenting it the problem goes away:
-- page 238 (Acrobat Reader page 254)
-- context IntermediateActions_LinkEndCreationData

Hope this minor bug report helps for a future release  :) 

Best regards

Fernando

